Ex BBNaija’s housemate Ka3na Jones has advised women to run away from men who monitor how they spend money. The single mother of one recounted her experience with the man she once met who told her to reduce how she spends money and how his questions portray insecurity. The divorced reality tv star noted this on her Instagram story. She said; “I met a guy for the first time and the first thing he said to me was ‘You need to reduce how you spend, ladies when you hear this, RUN!   Wizkid was nominated in wrong Grammy categories, says Naomi…     Five ex-BBNaija housemates making waves in Nollywood     I’m tired of Grammy nominations without winning – Femi Kuti   “He went on to inquire if my house here in the UK was mine or rented? I immediately said the rented (Black men) brother is insecure. “Ladies this is an automatic red flag.” Addressing the issue, Ka3na entertained fans’ opinions via “Question and Answer” on her Instastory. A fan said: “He feels intimidated and insecure @ d same time. Why should I manage what’s sufficient? It’s my money bro” Another fan said: “So that your money won’t finish. Go and google the story of a billionaire who later became poor”